abstract: >
  SHARD is a pipeline for aligning large language models toward safe, helpful
  responses without blunt refusals. It rewrites harmful prompts into safety-aligned
  alternatives using LLM-generated guidelines, then fine-tunes models via SFT and DPO
  on resulting preference pairs. Evaluated across seven models on the LinguaSafe benchmark.

keywords:
  - "LLM safety"
  - "alignment"
  - "supervised fine-tuning"
  - "direct preference optimization"
  - "LinguaSafe"

